  "text": "Given that the objective of this study is to identify factors that promoted or inhibited successful site start-up, it is important to be specific about the way \"success\" is defined in this context. Rather than successful start-up being expressed as one binary variable, in this case it is better characterized by success in achieving a number of outcomes (as in the Quint et al. [2011] SUCCESSFUL HOME VISITING START-UP 17 study of scaling up a college completion program). We consider four measures of successful site start-up, and these are similar to the \"implementation outcomes\" proposed by [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
